<subSubSection id="C374652CFFD5FFBED49CF9DF0DACF8F5" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BD136A7FFD5FFBED49CF9DF0DACF8F5" blockId="40.[151,1437,1652,2039]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFD5FFBED49CF9DF0C4AF91D" bold="true" box="[151,274,1652,1678]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D24FFD5FFBED5A8F9DF0E04F91D" authority="Jocque &amp; Baert, 2002" authorityName="Jocque &amp; Baert" authorityYear="2002" box="[419,860,1652,1679]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Tenedos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capote">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFD5FFBED5A8F9DF0F0BF91D" box="[419,595,1652,1678]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Tenedos capote</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B56FFD5FFBED657F9DF0E04F91D" author="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L." box="[604,860,1652,1679]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" pagination="67 - 173" refId="ref79332" refString="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L. (2002) A revision of the Neotropical spider genera Tenedos O. P. - Cambridge and Ishania Chamberlin (Araneae, Zodariidae). Bulletin de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique, Entomologie, 72, 67 - 173." type="journal article" year="2002">Jocqué &amp; Baert, 2002</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, are similar those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D24FFD5FFBED05FF9DE0D8AF921" authority="Jocque &amp; Baert, 2002" authorityName="Jocque &amp; Baert" authorityYear="2002" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Tenedos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barronus">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFD5FFBED05FF9DE0980F91D" box="[1108,1240,1652,1678]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">T. barronus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B56FFD5FFBED0EAF9DF0D8AF921" author="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L." pageId="40" pageNumber="41" pagination="67 - 173" refId="ref79332" refString="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L. (2002) A revision of the Neotropical spider genera Tenedos O. P. - Cambridge and Ishania Chamberlin (Araneae, Zodariidae). Bulletin de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique, Entomologie, 72, 67 - 173." type="journal article" year="2002">Jocqué &amp; Baert, 2002</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D24FFD5FFBED4D6F9320F1DF921" authority="Jocque &amp; Baert, 2002" authorityName="Jocque &amp; Baert" authorityYear="2002" box="[221,581,1688,1715]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Tenedos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoeferi">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFD5FFBED4D6F9320C1FF921" box="[221,327,1688,1714]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">T. hoeferi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B56FFD5FFBED545F9330F1DF921" author="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L." box="[334,581,1688,1715]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" pagination="67 - 173" refId="ref79332" refString="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L. (2002) A revision of the Neotropical spider genera Tenedos O. P. - Cambridge and Ishania Chamberlin (Araneae, Zodariidae). Bulletin de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique, Entomologie, 72, 67 - 173." type="journal article" year="2002">Jocqué &amp; Baert, 2002</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D24FFD5FFBED675F9320910F921" authority="Jocque &amp; Baert, 2002" authorityName="Jocque &amp; Baert" authorityYear="2002" box="[638,1096,1688,1715]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Tenedos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrangulatus">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFD5FFBED675F9320E13F921" box="[638,843,1688,1714]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">T. quadrangulatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B56FFD5FFBED759F9330910F921" author="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L." box="[850,1096,1688,1715]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" pagination="67 - 173" refId="ref79332" refString="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L. (2002) A revision of the Neotropical spider genera Tenedos O. P. - Cambridge and Ishania Chamberlin (Araneae, Zodariidae). Bulletin de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique, Entomologie, 72, 67 - 173." type="journal article" year="2002">Jocqué &amp; Baert, 2002</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, by having long, wide seminal receptacles (SR) curved towards median septum of Epigyne (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B56FFD5FFBED77EF91709CFF945" author="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L." box="[885,1175,1724,1751]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" pagination="67 - 173" refId="ref79332" refString="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L. (2002) A revision of the Neotropical spider genera Tenedos O. P. - Cambridge and Ishania Chamberlin (Araneae, Zodariidae). Bulletin de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique, Entomologie, 72, 67 - 173." type="journal article" year="2002">Jocqué &amp; Baert, 2002: 87</bibRefCitation>
, 100, 116, figs 10C–D, 18D–E, 33A–B; figs 12E–F; 13C–D; 27C–F), but can be distinguished by their wider seminal receptacles; knobshaped median field plate (MFP), wider than long, rounded in posterior border; wider than long atrium (A) almost as wide as anterior portion of median field plate; inverted V-shaped anterior border; larger spermathecae (S) (
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFD5FFBED164F8830DB0F8F5" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="43.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[199,1387,181,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-19@43.[199,1387,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURE 27. Tenedos capote Jocqué &amp; Baert, 2002. A–B. Female habitus (MCZ 54649): A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C–F. Female epigyne: C. Ventral view. D. Dorsal view. E. Ventral view. F. Dorsal view. Scale bars: A–B: 2mm; C–F: 500µm.Abbreviations: FD, fertilization ducts; LB, lateral borders; MFP, median field plate; S, spermathecae; SR, seminal receptacles." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520819" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520819/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Fig. 27C–F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
